@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 space-y-10">

    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="flex flex-col gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-2xl bg-sky-600 flex items-center justify-center shadow-lg shadow-sky-500/30">
                <span class="text-xs font-semibold text-white tracking-[0.18em]">NRL</span>
            </div>
            <div>
                <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-slate-50">
                    Privacy Policy
                </h1>
                <p class="text-sm text-slate-400">
                    How this application collects, uses, and protects personal data.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="text-xs text-slate-500">
            <p class="font-medium text-slate-300">Status</p>
            <p>Internal project – aviation obstacle reporting system.</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <!-- Layout: left overview, right main text -->
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1.1fr_2fr]">

        <!-- Overview / key points -->
        <aside class="space-y-4">
            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 shadow-xl backdrop-blur px-5 py-5 space-y-3">
                <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">
                    Summary
                </h2>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-300">
                    <li>• Accounts use email and encrypted passwords.</li>
                    <li>• Obstacle reports include height, description, and location data.</li>
                    <li>• Data is used only for aviation obstacle handling and system security.</li>
                    <li>• Admin users can review, approve, or delete reports.</li>
                    <li>• You can request deletion of your account and data.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 shadow-xl backdrop-blur px-5 py-5 space-y-3">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">
                    Data categories
                </h3>
                <dl class="space-y-2 text-xs text-slate-300">
                    <div>
                        <dt class="font-medium text-slate-200">Account</dt>
                        <dd>Email, password (hashed), optional profile fields.</dd>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <dt class="font-medium text-slate-200">Obstacle reports</dt>
                        <dd>Name, description, height, coordinates, geometry, timestamps, status.</dd>
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <dt class="font-medium text-slate-200">Technical</dt>
                        <dd>IP, browser metadata, session and authentication cookies.</dd>
                    </div>
                </dl>
            </div>

            <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 shadow-xl backdrop-blur px-5 py-4 space-y-2">
                <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100">Your rights</h3>
                <p class="text-xs text-slate-300">
                    You may request access, correction, export, or deletion of your personal data,
                    subject to applicable limitations and system requirements.
                </p>
            </div>
        </aside>

        <!-- Main content – English -->
        <section class="space-y-6 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 shadow-xl backdrop-blur px-6 py-6">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                1. Purpose of data processing
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                This application is used to register, review, and visualize aviation obstacles. Personal data is processed
                only to the extent necessary to provide authenticated access, handle obstacle reports, and maintain the
                security and integrity of the system.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                2. Data we collect
            </h2>

            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
                2.1 Account information
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                When you create an account, the application stores your email address and a hashed version of your password.
                Optional profile information, such as phone number, may also be stored if you choose to provide it.
                These data are used exclusively for authentication, account administration, and secure access control.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
                2.2 Obstacle reports
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                When you submit an obstacle, the application stores information such as obstacle name, height,
                description, geographic coordinates, geometry (GeoJSON), time of submission, and processing status
                (for example Pending, Approved, or Deleted). This information is necessary to maintain a reliable
                overview of reported aviation obstacles and to support administrative review.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">
                2.3 Technical and security-related information
            </h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                For operational and security purposes, the system may log technical information such as IP address,
                browser metadata, server logs, and session or authentication cookies. These data are used solely to
                operate and secure the application and are not used for profiling or marketing.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                3. Legal basis
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                Personal data is processed on the basis of user consent, legitimate interest (for example system security
                and quality of obstacle data), and, where applicable, contractual necessity in order to provide access to
                the application’s functionality.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                4. Access and roles
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                Access to data is restricted using role-based access control:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-slate-200 space-y-1">
                <li><span class="font-medium">Administrators</span> can view and manage obstacle reports, including approving or deleting them.</li>
                <li><span class="font-medium">Authenticated users</span> can submit obstacles and view reports, but cannot approve or delete them.</li>
                <li><span class="font-medium">Unauthenticated users</span> have no access to account data or administrative functions.</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                Data is not sold or shared with third parties, unless required by law or necessary for compliance with
                applicable regulations.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                5. Storage and retention
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                Account information is kept for as long as the account is active. Obstacle reports are stored as long as
                they are considered relevant for the system’s purpose or until they are deleted during administrative
                maintenance. Technical logs are retained only for as long as necessary to ensure security and operation.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                6. Your rights
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                Subject to applicable law, you have the right to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-slate-200 space-y-1">
                <li>Request access to the personal data stored about you.</li>
                <li>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
                <li>Request deletion of your account and associated personal data.</li>
                <li>Request export of your personal data where technically feasible.</li>
                <li>Object to or request restriction of certain types of processing.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                7. Security measures
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                The application uses industry-standard technical and organizational measures, including HTTPS, secure
                password hashing, authorization based on roles, and restricted database access. The system is regularly
                updated to reduce the risk of unauthorized access and data breaches.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                8. Cookies
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                The application uses cookies primarily for authentication and session management. No cookies are used
                for advertising or third-party tracking. Without these cookies, core functionality such as login and
                secure navigation may not work as intended.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                9. Changes to this policy
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
                This Privacy Policy may be updated to reflect changes in functionality, security requirements, or
                applicable laws and regulations. Material changes will be made available through this page.
            </p>
        </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Norwegian version -->
    <section class="space-y-4 rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/80 shadow-xl backdrop-blur px-6 py-6">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-2">
            <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-50">
                Personvernerklæring (norsk sammendrag)
            </h2>
            <span class="text-[11px] px-2 py-1 rounded-full bg-slate-800 text-slate-300 border border-slate-600">
                Informasjonsside – ikke juridisk bindende oversettelse
            </span>
        </div>

        <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
            Denne applikasjonen brukes til å registrere, behandle og visualisere luftfartshindringer. Personopplysninger
            behandles kun i den grad det er nødvendig for å gi sikker innlogging, håndtere innmeldte hindringer og
            ivareta sikker og stabil drift av løsningen.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">Hvilke opplysninger samles inn?</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-sm text-slate-200 space-y-1">
            <li><span class="font-medium">Kontoopplysninger:</span> e-postadresse, passord (lagret kryptert), samt eventuell valgfri informasjon du selv legger inn.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Hindringsdata:</span> navn, høyde, beskrivelse, geografisk plassering (koordinater og geometri), tidspunkt for registrering og status.</li>
            <li><span class="font-medium">Tekniske data:</span> IP-adresse, nettleserinfo, sesjons- og innloggingscookies, samt grunnleggende driftslogger.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">Formål og tilgang</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
            Opplysningene brukes for å muliggjøre registrering og kvalitetssikring av hindringer, og for å gi
            administratorer mulighet til å godkjenne eller slette rapporter. Vanlige brukere kan registrere og se
            innmeldinger, men ikke godkjenne eller slette dem. Opplysninger selges ikke videre og deles ikke med
            tredjeparter, med mindre det følger av lov.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">Lagring og rettigheter</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
            Kontoopplysninger lagres så lenge kontoen er aktiv. Hindringsdata lagres så lenge de anses relevante, eller
            til de slettes som del av administrativ vedlikehold. Du kan be om innsyn, korrigering eller sletting av
            dine personopplysninger, innenfor rammene av gjeldende regelverk og systemets tekniske begrensninger.
        </p>

        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-slate-100 mt-2">Sikkerhet og cookies</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-200">
            Løsningen bruker kryptert kommunikasjon (HTTPS), sikker håndtering av passord og tilgangsstyring basert på
            roller. Cookies brukes hovedsakelig for innlogging og sesjonshåndtering. Det brukes ikke cookies til
            markedsføring eller tredjeparts sporing.
        </p>
    </section>
</div>
